items.name: Object_Text
items.content: # =================================================================== # # Script: Object_Text # # $$COPYRIGHT$$ # # =================================================================== class Object_Text extends gs.Object_Visual @objectCodecBlackList = ["parent"] ###* * A game object used for custom texts in a scene. * * @module gs * @class Object_Text * @extends gs.Object_Visual * @memberof gs * @constructor ### constructor: (data) -> super ###* * The object's bitmap used for visual presentation. * @property bitmap * @type gs.Bitmap ### @bitmap = null ###* * The font used for the text. * @property font * @type gs.Font ### @font = new Font(gs.Fonts.TEXT) ###* * Indicates if word-wrap is enabled. If true line-breaks are automatically added. * @property wordWrap * @type boolean ### @wordWrap = no ###* * The domain the object belongs to. * @property domain * @type string ### @domain = "com.degica.vnm.default" ###* * The object's source rectangle. It controls which part of the object's image is used * for visual presentation. * @property srcRect * @type gs.Rect ### @srcRect = new Rect() ###* * The object's mask to execute masking-effects on it. * @property mask * @type gs.Mask ### @mask = new gs.Mask() ###* * Indicates if the object's visual presentation should be mirrored horizontally. * @property mirror * @type boolean ### @mirror = false ###* * The text to display. * @property text * @type string ### @text = "" ###* * The rotation-angle of the picture in degrees. The rotation center depends on the * anchor-point. * @property angle * @type number ### @angle = 0 ###* * The color tone of the object used for the visual presentation. * @property tone * @type gs.Tone ### @tone = new Tone(0, 0, 0, 0) ###* * The color of the object used for the visual presentation. * @property color * @type gs.Color ### @color = new Color(255, 255, 255, 0) ###* * The text-renderer used to render the text. * @property textRenderer * @type gs.Component_TextRenderer ### @textRenderer = new gs.Component_TextRenderer() @textRenderer.object = this ###* * The object's animator-component to execute different kind of animations like move, rotate, etc. on it. * @property animator * @type gs.Component_Animator ### @animator = new gs.Component_Animator() ###* * The object's visual-component to display the game object on screen. * @property visual * @type gs.Component_Sprite ### @visual = new gs.Component_Sprite(no) ###* * The object's behavior component for the text-specific behavior. * @property behavior * @type gs.Component_TextBehavior ### @behavior = new gs.Component_TextBehavior() @addComponent(@visual) @addComponent(@behavior) @addComponent(@animator) @componentsFromDataBundle(data) #@update() ###* * Restores the game object from a data-bundle. * * @method restore * @param {Object} data - The data-bundle. ### restore: (data) -> super(data) @srcRect = gs.Rect.fromObject(data.srcRect) @mask = gs.Mask.fromObject(data.mask) ###* * Serializes the object into a data-bundle. * * @method toDataBundle * @return {Object} The data-bundle. ### toDataBundle: -> components = @componentsToDataBundle(gs.Component_Animation) result = { components: components, dstRect: @dstRect, srcRect: @srcRect, opacity: @opacity, origin: @origin, offset: @offset, anchor: @anchor, zIndex: @zIndex, mask: @mask.toDataBundle(), motionBlur: @motionBlur, zoom: @zoom, angle: @angle, mirror: @mirror, text: @text, formatting: @formatting } return result gs.Object_Text = Object_Text
